    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Personal Finance Telegram Bot: Automated Receipt Tracking & Expense Queries\n\nThis workflow turns your Telegram bot into a smart personal finance assistant. Send receipt photos/PDFs or text, and AI (Google Gemini) extracts date, amount (in MYR), description, and category — then logs it to Google Sheets with the image uploaded to Google Drive.\n\nAsk natural language questions like \"How much did I spend last month?\" or \"Total on food this month?\" and get AI-powered summaries, breakdowns, and insights using your logged data.\n\nPerfect for effortless expense tracking without manual entry!\n\n## How it works\n- Telegram Trigger detects incoming messages/photos/documents.\n- Switch routes: images/PDFs → OCR/analysis/upload → AI parsing → log to Sheets.\n- Text queries → AI agent queries Sheets data + calculator for answers.\n- Confirmation/summary replies sent back to Telegram.\n\n## Setup steps\n1. Connect credentials: Telegram API, Google Sheets (OAuth2), Google Drive, Google Gemini API.\n2. Update Google Sheets node with your spreadsheet ID (pre-filled, but verify).\n3. Update Google Drive upload nodes with your folder ID for receipts.\n4. Activate the workflow and send a test message/receipt to your bot.\n\nLive Google Sheet (Template)\nYou can make a copy of the exact sheet the bot uses:\nhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nTD4c1_DAuDJAC9oDvgdNkp3-Fl5hT6t25DkiR3-LsE/edit?usp=sharing\n\nJust click File → Make a copy and use your copy’s ID in the workflow.\n\n## Image Quality Tip\nFor best OCR results, send images and pdf only in Telegram. Tap the paperclip icon → File → select your image. This preserves original quality without compression.\n\n## Customization tips\n- Edit AI Agent prompts to add/remove categories or refine parsing.\n- Adjust memory window or add more tools for advanced queries.",
        "height": 992,
        "width": 688
      },
      "id": "07b0eaa0-88b3-4e66-bdfb-5d19e592b9c4",
      "name": "Sticky Note4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        368,
        240
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "for (const item of $input.all()) {\n  if (item.binary) {\n    for (const key of Object.keys(item.binary)) {\n      const file = item.binary[key];\n      const ext = (file.fileExtension || \"\").toLowerCase();\n      const name = (file.fileName || \"\").toLowerCase();\n\n      if (file.mimeType === \"application/octet-stream\") {\n        if (ext === \"heic\" || name.endsWith(\".heic\")) {\n          file.mimeType = \"image/heic\";\n        } else if (ext === \"pdf\" || name.endsWith(\".pdf\")) {\n          file.mimeType = \"application/pdf\";\n        } else if (ext === \"png\" || name.endsWith(\".png\")) {\n          file.mimeType = \"image/png\";\n        } else {\n          file.mimeType = \"image/jpeg\";\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\nreturn $input.all();"
      },
      "id": "8608a35c-1943-4046-927e-40b3497fad79",
      "name": "Fix MIME Type",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        2864,
        464
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const allItems = $input.all();\n\nlet textContent = \"\";\nlet driveLink = \"\";\n\n// Flatten everything from the aggregated data array\nconst aggregatedData = allItems[0]?.json?.data || [];\n\n// Get Gemini text\nconst geminiResult = aggregatedData.find(item => item.content?.parts);\nif (geminiResult) {\n  textContent = geminiResult.content.parts.map(p => p.text || \"\").join(\" \");\n}\n\n// Get Drive link\nconst driveFile = aggregatedData.find(item => item.webViewLink && item.kind === \"drive#file\");\nif (driveFile) {\n  driveLink = driveFile.webViewLink;\n}\n\nif (!textContent.trim()) {\n  textContent = \"No readable text found. Please ensure the image contains clear text.\";\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: { extractedText: textContent, driveLink } }];"
      },
